Git is a version control system us track our code, and make changes to code in a better and specific manner. 

Github is where you STORE code.

-- Git Commands -- :

Clone a repo: "git clone -SSH Key-" 

Show ALL files (even hidden): "ls -la"

Shows all files that were changed, updated, or deleted: "git status"

Starts to track and add the new things you added that are untracked : "git add ."

Commit the changes and code: "git commit -m"

Push commit to GitHub & make it public in the repo: " git push origin master"

